This paper deals with probabilistic similarity queries on uncertain data, which is a topic that falls under the umbrella of database systems (cs.DB). The paper proposes a novel pruning criterion that uses probabilistic density functions, which is a technique commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also introduces an iterative filter-refinement strategy, which is a technique commonly used in data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). The paper uses geometric pruning filters, which is a technique commonly used in machine learning and pattern recognition (cs.LG). Finally, the paper deals with probability bounds, which is a topic that falls under the umbrella of information theory (cs.IT).
